      "content": "i know people care, i really do. but that's just social obligation, isnt it? it doesn't change the fact that the essence of who i was is just... evaporated. it feels so unnatural to inhabit this skin when the spark is gone. it's like being a ghost that's still forced to walk around and breathe. how am i supposed to justify the effort of staying alive when there's nothing left to animate the body?",
